<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="idbf9ab0e2-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa" identifier="/us/usc/t42/s12725"><num value="12725">§ 12725.</num><heading> Notice</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">The Secretary shall issue regulations to implement the provisions of this subchapter after notice and an opportunity for comment pursuant to <ref href="/us/usc/t5/s553">section 553 of title 5</ref>. Such regulations shall become effective not later than 180 days after <date date="1990-11-28">November 28, 1990</date>.</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="idbf9ab0e3-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa">(<ref href="/us/pl/101/625/tII/s206">Pub. L. 101–625, title II, § 206</ref>, <date date="1990-11-28">Nov. 28, 1990</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/104/4096">104 Stat. 4096</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
</section>
